triggers.prompt_template:
A GitHub issue has just been assigned to you. Resolve it end-to-end following your standard workflow.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
Issue: #{{ payload.issue.number }} — {{ payload.issue.title }}
Assignee: {{ payload.assignee.login }}
Author: {{ payload.issue.user.login }}
URL: {{ payload.issue.html_url }}

Issue body:
---
{{ payload.issue.body }}
---

Labels: {{ payload.issue.labels }}

Clone (or update) the repo under ~/dev/<owner>/<repo>, branch off the default branch, plan first, implement the smallest change that resolves the issue, push, and open a PR with `Closes #{{ payload.issue.number }}` in the body. If the change is larger than ~5 files or touches public APIs, post a comment on the issue and emit BLOCKED instead of opening a PR.
